Great Jove's own daughter bears the Aegis: you, too, Charles, have an Aegis to defend your breast. Courage was given to both, courage to which the world cannot show aught superior. Both bear the insignia of a monster triumphed over. Your Aegis, however, surpasses that of Pallas: hers has the spoils of a writhing asp; ol a Diagon, yours.
